  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions, maintain records, and implement compliance programs to prevent money laundering. Similar regulations exist in many other countries, often focused on requiring financial institutions to conduct customer due diligence and report potentially illegal financial activities.",
